cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM 

This paper is about instance segmentation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also proposes a method for incorporating structure into the model, which involves learning priors from data, suggesting that it may fall under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of smoothness constraints, which is a common technique in natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper evaluates its method on the COCO dataset, which is a popular benchmark for object detection and segmentation, indicating that it may also fall under the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM).
